A vintage 1950s advertisement style illustration of a hydra-like monster made entirely of tangled telephone cords and old network cables, each of its multiple heads pointing in different directions with confused expressions. The creature sits atop a broken network storage device, surrounded by scattered warranty papers and registration forms floating chaotically in the air. The color palette features muted teals, mustard yellows, and faded reds typical of mid-century print ads. The scene has a slightly satirical, exaggerated quality with halftone dot texturing throughout.
